docs.abstract: Darrell Issa, the former nine-term congressman, is the latest Republican to launch a bid against Representative Duncan Hunter, who was indicted last August.
docs.snippet: Darrell Issa, the former nine-term congressman, is the latest Republican to launch a bid against Representative Duncan Hunter, who was indicted last August.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Darrell Issa, the former nine-term congressman from California, will try to return to Congress by challenging Representative Duncan Hunter, who was indicted last year, setting up a clash among two Trump allies for one of Republicans’ most endangered seats.

headline.main: In California, Former Congressman Darrell Issa Will Challenge Indicted Congressman Duncan Hunter
headline.print_headline: Indicted Lawmaker Faces An Experienced Challenger

docs.abstract: The speaker’s “coldblooded” plan for defeating President Trump, who she worries would challenge a slim Democratic victory in 2020, focuses on moderate voters and avoiding a protracted impeachment bid.
docs.snippet: The speaker’s “coldblooded” plan for defeating President Trump, who she worries would challenge a slim Democratic victory in 2020, focuses on moderate voters and avoiding a protracted impeachment bid.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi does not believe President Trump can be removed through impeachment — the only way to do it, she said this week, is to defeat him in 2020 by a margin so “big” he cannot challenge the legitimacy of a Democratic victory.

headline.main: Pelosi Warns Democrats: Stay in the Center or Trump May Contest Election Results
headline.print_headline: ‘Own the Center-Left,’ Pelosi Tells Democrats, Or Risk a Disputed Win

docs.lead_paragraph: Ten candidates vying for the 2020 Democratic presidential nomination took the stage Thursday night in Houston for the third round of debates. docs.abstract: Newly declassified files reveal a secret court fight over the F.B.I.’s procedures for searching for Americans’ messages within a warrantless surveillance program’s repository.
docs.snippet: Newly declassified files reveal a secret court fight over the F.B.I.’s procedures for searching for Americans’ messages within a warrantless surveillance program’s repository.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A federal judge secretly ruled last year that the F.B.I.’s procedures for searching for Americans’ emails within a repository of intercepted messages that were gathered without a warrant violated Fourth Amendment privacy rights, newly declassified files showed.

headline.main: F.B.I. Practices for Intercepted Emails Violated 4th Amendment, Judge Ruled
headline.print_headline: Judge Says F.B.I. Tactics Violated Right of Privacy
